        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-25 06:02:24.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nTwo questions:\n- why is this not handled at the point where NEED_INDEX is first set?\n- does this correctly handle the case of combined MGS/MDS, since IS_MGS() is true there, but the index is still needed?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3e61676f5d1c1e0ddd9c65c1944abcfebeb61eff",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2012-09-25 11:32:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAnother question is will the MGS support using a index in the future? If that is the case then the fix is needed in mkfs_lustre.c. Yes you are right about handling the case of the MDT and MGT being the same device.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
